    "title": "[ U.S. DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE  |  COMPLEX TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY REHABILITATION CLINICAL RESEARCH AWARD ]",
    "slug": "us-department-of-defense-complex-traumatic-brain-i",
    "absolute_slug": "https://memento.epfl.ch/event/us-department-of-defense-complex-traumatic-brain-i",
    "lang": "fr",
    "state": "Published",
    "description": "<strong>Aim: </strong>The FY17/18 PH/TBIRP CTRR–CRA Program Announcement supports applied and translational research to advance the development of knowledge and materiel products for rehabilitation and restoration of function following TBI. The overarching goals of this award are to address TBI-related impairments and deficits including sensory, sensorimotor, and cognitive dysfunction to (1) develop and validate rehabilitation outcome measures; (2) define and evaluate mechanisms of injury progression or recovery associated with rehabilitation interventions; and (3) improve clinician-driven assessment strategies to guide return-to-duty decision making.<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<strong>Funding</strong>: Up to USD $2 million<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<strong>Eligibility: </strong>Independent investigators at all academic levels (or equivalent) are eligible to submit an application. Applications must include preliminary data and/or published data from the literature that are relevant to complex TBI and support the rationale for the proposed research project. Preclinical studies using animals<strong> are not supported</strong> by this Program Announcement.<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<strong>How to Apply</strong>: Submission is a two-step process, starting with a pre-application which may lead to invitation to submit a full application. Pre-applications are made through the <a href=\"https://ebrap.org/\">eBRAP</a> portal. Full applications are submitted through <a href=\"file://scxdata/CommunDAR%24/4-INTERNATIONAL-FUNDING/4.8-US%20GRANTS/4.8.2%20US%20Federal%20Funding%20Bodies/4.8-DOD/grants.gov\">grants.gov</a>.<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<strong>Pre-Application Deadline: </strong>11 October 2017, 5:00 pm EDT<br>\r\n<strong>Invitation to Submit an Application: </strong>10 November 2017<br>\r\n<strong>Application Deadline: </strong>3 January 2018, 11:59 pm EST<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<strong>Further information</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>More information on the program can by searching <a href=\"grants.gov\">grants.gov</a> for the following funding opportunity: W81XWH-17-CTRR-CRA</li>\r\n</ul>",
