    "translation_id": "69665",
    "title": "[BRIDGE I RESEARCH FUNDING]",
    "slug": "bridge-i-research-funding-6",
    "absolute_slug": "https://memento.epfl.ch/event/bridge-i-research-funding-6",
    "lang": "en",
    "state": "Published",
    "description": "<strong>Aim:</strong> BRIDGE is a joint programme conducted by the <strong>Swiss National Science Foundation</strong> (SNSF) and the<strong> Commission for Technology and Innovation</strong> (CTI). It offers new funding opportunities at the intersection of basic research and science-based innovation, thereby supplementing the funding activities of the two organisations.<br>\r\n<strong>Bridge Proof of Concept</strong> projects support young researchers (see eligibility criteria <a href=\"http://bridge.ch/en/for-young-researchers-proof-of-concept/\">on the website</a>) who aim to develop an application or service based on their own research findings. These projects may feature any type of innovation or research field.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>Submission deadline:</strong> 04.06.2018<br>\r\n<strong>Funding:</strong> Max. CHF 130,000 per year. It covers your salary and any costs that are directly linked to the execution of your project<br>\r\n<strong>Duration:</strong> 12 months. It may be extended once for a maximum of six months.<br>\r\n<strong>For more information:</strong> Please check the <strong><a href=\"http://bridge.ch/en/for-young-researchers-proof-of-concept/\">BRIDGE' website</a> </strong>and carefully read the <strong><a href=\"http://www.snf.ch/SiteCollectionDocuments/Bridge_PoC_Call_03_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">guidelines</a></strong> (especially the formal requirements)<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>Applicants must contact the <a href=\"mailto:research@epfl.ch?subject=Bridge%20-%20Proof%20of%20Concept%20call\" target=\"_blank\">Research Office</a></strong> for the second required support letter (from the institution) as soon as possible, <strong><u>at least 10 days before the deadline</u></strong>.                      <br>\r\n<br>\r\n ",
